# Phases 4-6: Scale, PWA & Premium

This plan covers the final stretch: the engagement "Hype" engine, mobile optimization (PWA), and a new Premium revenue model.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Premium Logic**: $10/mo will be tracked via a new `subscription_tier` column in the `profiles` table. Verified badges will be displayed next to usernames for these users.

> [!NOTE]
> **Storage Resilience**: We will prioritize Cloudflare R2 for all users, but implement a fallback to Supabase Storage for Premium users if R2 latency is high (as requested).

## Proposed Changes

### [Phase 4: Shorts & Hype Engine]

#### [MODIFY] [WatchClient.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/app/watch/[id]/WatchClient.tsx)
- Implement "Hype" (Upvote) animation and database persistence.
- Add "Global Vibe" score leaderboard.

#### [MODIFY] [VideoCard.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/components/VideoCard.tsx)
- Add "Trending" badge for high-velocity videos.
- Add "Verified" badge for Premium creators.

### [Phase 5: Mobile PWA & Push]

#### [NEW] [manifest.json](file:///C:/GOLive/public/manifest.json)
Standard PWA manifest for "Add to Home Screen" support.

#### [NEW] [sw.ts](file:///C:/GOLive/public/sw.ts)
Service worker for basic caching and offline support.

### [Phase 6: Revenue & Verification]

#### [MODIFY] [Subscription Logic]
- Create `/api/premium/subscribe` endpoint.
- Update `profiles` table to include `tier` and `is_verified`.

## Bug Fix: AI Clipping Core

- **FFmpeg Path**: I will switch to a "bundled binary" approach or use a more resilient path resolution that handles Next.js Turbopack virtualization (fixing the `ENOENT` error).

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Test `/shorts` on mobile viewport (already verified working once, but will re-check after Hype engine updates).
- Verify `is_verified` flag correctly renders the badge.

### Manual Verification
- User to test the "Clip & Post" flow once fixed.
- Verify "Verified" badge appears on Creator Dashboard.
